As ballots begin to be sent out, Ms Truss promised in a letter to Conservative MPs that if elected she would "seize the opportunities of Brexit" and "level up in a Conservative way". However, Sky News chief political correspondent Jon Craig accused Ms Truss of using the letter to "attack" Mr Sunak's handling of the economy as chancellor. He said: "In an attack on Sunak, she said: 'We cannot continue to have business-as-usual and I have a bold plan to get our economy back on track. I will lower taxes to spark economic growth and reward people for working hard.'" FOLLOW BELOW FOR UPDATESâ€¦.